aration Programs Faculty Profile Responsibilities of the Associate Dean for Educator Preparation Programs Teacher Education Council Undergraduate, Post-Baccalaureate, and Advanced Educator Preparation Programs Educator Preparation Programs Assessment Committee Assessment/Data Management for  Educator Preparation: TK20 Assessment System Coordinator for Accreditation of Educator Preparation Programs Oversees Clinical Practice for Educator Preparation Coordinates with Federal, State and Local Education Agencies: PEDS, Title II, SBEC, THECB, School Districts Dr. Gwenn Pasco Assistant Dean for Educator Certification and Undergraduate Academic Services Responsibilities of the Assistant Dean for Educator Certification and Undergraduate Academic Services Director of the Student Advising Office (SAO) Oversees TExES Advising Office (TAO) Orientations: Freshman, Transfer, Parent Preview Days and Prospective Student Recruitment Communicates with state agencies, TEA, SBEC, and provides data collection for state and federal reports and mandates Recommends graduates and undergraduates for initial and supplemental certifications Coordinates with departments about student and academic affairs Advising Task Force Committee member Administration of College Commencement - Senior Academic Budget Officer   Responsibilities of the Senior Academic Budget Officer Oversees and reconciles budgets Approves and signs all HRM forms and budgetary transfers Records and manages faculty and staff records Compiles enrollments and semester credit hours reports Building Representative for Matthews Hall DeeAnna Oliveira College Research Officer Responsibilities of the College Research Officer Initial contact for grant initiation Assistance in finding appropriate grants Pre- and post-grant budgets Grant budget processing support and tracking Ms. Jo Monahan Embedded Librarian Responsibilities of the Embedded Librarian Support information needs of faculty and students Provide group or individual instructio